A 'jealous and controlling' teenager has been found guilty of murdering his pregnant 16-year-old girlfriend with a scarf and will serve at least 14 years in jail.

Aston Robinson, 18, repeatedly punched Kayleigh-Anne Palmer - who was 24 weeks pregnant -before strangling her so she would 'be quiet'.

Robinson lashed out at the schoolgirl after getting into an argument about boys she had spoken to, Bristol Crown Court heard.

