In a statement they said: 'Justice has been done for Kayleigh and we wish to thank the jury for their verdict which will help us bring closure on what has been a very distressing time.

'Kay will be remembered by her family and friends for her huge personality and radiant smile and our lives are so much richer for having known and loved her.

